In patients with impaired renal function, parenteral nutrition solutions containing TRAVASOL should be administered with caution. Frequent clinical evaluation and laboratory tests to monitor renal function such as serum electrolytes (especially phosphate and potassium) and fluid balance should 
                              be conducted [see Dosage and Administration (2.6), Warnings and Precautions (5.10)

